# <type>[optional scope]: <summary>
#
# Rules:
#   - Use Conventional Commits: type(scope): description or type: description
#   - Use imperative mood
#   - Use a scope when it adds clarity
#   - Keep the subject concise and specific
#   - Keep it under 50 characters when practical
#   - Body is optional and may add context
#   - Footer is optional and may add references or breaking changes
#   - Use BREAKING CHANGE: or ! for breaking changes
#   - When a title field expects one line, output only the subject line
#
# Allowed types:
#   feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, chore, ci, revert
#
# Examples:
#   feat(pattern): add starter groove presets
#   fix(protocol): correct lane-chunked pattern encoding
#   docs(readme): clarify PO-32 transfer workflow
#   docs: update README usage notes
#   fix(ci): invoke commit checker with sh
#
# SemVer guidance:
#   feat     -> minor release
#   fix/perf -> patch release
#   !        -> breaking change / major release
